In the global in vivo toxicology market, product categories such as consumables and instruments play a crucial role in facilitating toxicology studies. Testing types including biologics toxicology, cytotoxicity assays, and ADME-Tox testing are essential for evaluating the safety profile of pharmaceuticals and chemicals. Toxicity endpoints tested vary across systemic toxicity, dermal toxicity, and genotoxicity, among others. Test facilities can either be outsourced or conducted in-house, depending on the specific requirements of the study and the resources available.

