Another significant factor influencing the in vivo toxicology market is the increasing awareness of the importance of early-stage toxicity testing in drug development. With the rising costs and time pressures associated with bringing a new drug to market, pharmaceutical companies are recognizing the value of conducting comprehensive toxicology studies early in the drug development process. This proactive approach not only helps to identify potential safety issues at an early stage but also improves the overall success rate of drug candidates in clinical trials. Market players such as WuXi AppTec and SGS SA are catering to this growing demand for early-stage toxicity testing by offering a wide range of services tailored to different stages of drug development.

